    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Found the root cause. When `b-tester` blocks user `a-tester`, then `a-tester` is no longer a contact to `b-tester` (that's very strange, cause block user action should be only local to `b-tester`, apparently it isn't). Messages don't appear anymore, because in nim-status-client we [ignore messages from non-contacts](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/b5e317db4dc702c7de742d07d55dc9e38bcd56bf/src/app_service/service/message/service.nim#L182-L184).\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33099791/198040519-1cb5cabf-d5f2-43e2-a361-1d1662086b77.mp4\r\n\r\n",
