    "body": "Ah ok that's indeed a bit confusing, but I see the reasoning.\r\n\r\nThe block action is now propagated and it removes the mutual contact status.\r\n\r\nSo in theory, this is not a bug, because it's normal that you can't contact the person anymore. \r\nThe problem is that we don't make it clear. The person that unblocks should have a message or button that says that they need to add the contact again. I'm not sure if there is a design for that, similarly to the `Unblock` button that appears next to the input box?",
